source.lettering: Medicinal Plants (I) Papaver somniferum, Linn. n.o. Papaveraceae. common names: bale-wort; cheesebowl; opium poppy; peony poppy; white poppy. French: pavot blanc. German: mohn; gartenmohn; schlafmohn. products: opium (dried latex); dried fruits (poppy-heads); and (maw) seeds (non-poisonous). active principles: morphine and many other alkaloids
